Here you can find a collection of bytebeat programs, some of them rather involved.




FOCUS
===============
[Live Version Here](http://greggman.com/downloads/examples/html5bytebeat/html5bytebeat.html#t=1&e=0&s=11000&)

[Minified Version Here](http://greggman.com/downloads/examples/html5bytebeat/html5bytebeat.html#t=1&e=0&s=11000&)




Bytebeat version of "**Focus**", made by **DoubleyouDashM**  (Wiebe-Marten Wijnja)  (http://www.wmmusic.nl)

Original song written by **Niamh Houston** (Chipzel) (http://chipzelmusic.bandcamp.com/)

for the game Super Hexagon, which was made by **Terry Cavanagh** (http://distractionware.com/)

===

Why did I make this?
--------------------
 - I love Super Hexagon
 - I love Chipzel's Music and Chiptune in general
 - I wanted to learn more about and Waveform creation in computers
 - I wanted to learn more about procedural content genration. (Yep, although the output from this code is deterministic, it is procedural)


Features:
---------
 - Speedup or slowdown as much as you want without losing quality
 - Play backwards!
 - When compressed, only 3452 bytes:  1/1000th of the size of Focus as .mp3(actually a lossy format) which is +- 2.5 Megabytes.
	(Note that further compression should also be easily possible. There's lots here that could be code-golfed)
